<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,653]" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,493,338,364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. D. Chu et C. S. Chao" authorityYear="1980" box="[521,783,338,364]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Indocalamus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="emeiensis">
<emphasis box="[521,783,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">Indocalamus emeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[953,1154,338,364]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">Sichuan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1234,338,364]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1251,1320,338,365]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1108,1130]" captionTargetBox="[214,1380,214,1060]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[183,1403,190,1083]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Geographical distribution of Indocalamus emeiensis (red pentacles)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404573/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with three distributed localities found so far, i.e., Muping, Sanlang and Emei Mountain. It usually grows in the understory of evergreen broad-leaved forests or dank valleys at elevations of 
<quantity box="[844,988,410,437]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.85" pageId="8" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="1025.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="850.0">850–1200 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,653]" box="[189,1003,446,473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,323,446,472]" pageId="8" pageNumber="61">Phenology:</emphasis>
—New shoots from August to October. Flowering unknown.
</paragraph>
